            SIZING["Subnet Sizing Guide
─────────────────────────────────────
/25  →  ~60 nodes    (126 IPs)
/24  →  ~120 nodes   (254 IPs)
/22  →  ~500 nodes   (1,022 IPs)
/20  →  ~2,000 nodes (4,094 IPs)"]:::sizingStyle

            NODE1["GCE Node 1
10.0.0.2 — 10.0.0.3"]:::nodeStyle
            NODE2["GCE Node 2
10.0.0.4 — 10.0.0.5"]:::nodeStyle
            NODE3["GCE Node ...N
10.0.x.x — 10.0.x.x"]:::nodeStyle
        end

        NAT["Cloud NAT
─────────────────────────
Outbound-only egress
Nodes have NO public IPs
All outbound via NAT GW"]:::natStyle

        ADVANTAGE["GCE Advantage — No Secondary IP Ranges Required
Only ONE primary subnet range is needed.
Simple flat network topology — no pod or service CIDRs."]:::advantageStyle
